  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When you want to go beyond the effects provided by a shape node's properties, you can take full control of its stroking or filling by using the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshapenode/1519784-strokeshader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshapenode/1519629-fillshader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " properties, respectively. To do that, you supply custom OpenGL ES shader code embedded within a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object. Custom shaders allow you to create custom effects, such as dashed lines and gradient strokes, and custom fills, such as checkerboards and random patterns. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Customize a Shape Node's Stroke",
          "anchor": "2647274"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Shape nodes have two additional stroke-related properties that extend the properties defined by "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ":  "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "table",
          "header": "row",
          "rows": [
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Symbol declaration"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Type"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Description"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "float u_path_length;"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Uniform"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "The total length of the path, in points."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ],
            [
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "float v_path_distance;"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "Varying"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ],
              [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "text": "The distance along the path, in points."
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            ]
          ],
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2647278",
            "title": "Table 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "By dividing the distance along the path by the total length of the path, you get the normalized position (between "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "0"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "1"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ") of each point along a shape node's path and use it to construct the color of each pixel along the shape node's stroke. The following code shows how you create a custom shader to do this:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "void main() {",
            "    float normalisedPosition = v_path_distance / u_path_length;",
            "    gl_FragColor = vec4(normalisedPosition, normalisedPosition, 0.0, 1.0);",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "occ",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2647279",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The generated shape node looks like this:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2647280",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2647280",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Alternatively, by casting both symbols to integers and using the modulo operator, you get the same shape node with a shader that generates a dashed line, as shown in the following code: "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "void main() {",
            "    int stripe = int(u_path_length) / 150;",
            "    int h = int(v_path_distance) / stripe % 2;",
            "    gl_FragColor = float4(h);",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "occ",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2647281",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The generated shape node looks like this:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-2647282",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2647282",
                "title": "Figure 2"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Customize a Shape Node's Fill",
          "anchor": "2647275"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You create a custom fill for a shape node by writing shader code and embedding it within an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object. Assigning the shader to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshapenode/1519629-fillshader"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property overrides the appearance that would otherwise be defined by "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshapenode/1520154-fillcolor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/spritekit/skshapenode/1519956-filltexture"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The following shader code demonstrates filling a shape node with a simple checkerboard texture. Inside the shader, the variables "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "h"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "v"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " would, on their own, form horizontal and vertical stripes. The exclusive or operator, "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "^"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", creates the checkerboard pattern from those stripes. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "void main() {",
            "    int size = 20;",
            "    int h = int(v_tex_coord.x * u_texture_size.x) / size % 2;",
            "    int v = int(v_tex_coord.y * u_texture_size.y) / size % 2;",
            "    gl_FragColor = float4(v ^ h, v ^ h, v ^ h, 1.0);",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "occ",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2647283",
            "title": "Listing 3"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The generated shape node looks like this:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
